title.53: Marvel Super Hero Contest of Champions (1982) #3
title.74: Marvel Super Hero Contest of Champions (1982) #2

description.1: Can the rebels prevent the construction on an Imperial base on Serphidi?
description.9: Come on, make Logan's day. He dares you. Frank Miller, artist extraordinaire, shows off Wolverine's shiny claws and winning smile in the feral mutant's first limited series.
description.10: The threat of Silvermane rachets up when he gets a new cyborg body. Can Spider-Man stop Cloak and Dagger from killing Silvermane?
description.13: Spider-Man and the Human Torch take on SPEED DEMON! But when the sinister speedster proves too much for the two young guns, salvation leaps in from a very unexpected place!
description.14: The final confrontation in the war for the SAVAGE LAND! A technological prison with a sole occupant - DEATHLOK! A nightmare turned real for IRON MAN!
description.15: The Inhuman Black Bolt answers the call to help Dazzler take down the Absorbing Man!
description.16: Matt's putting pressure on Heather to say "yes" to his marriage proposal, but how well does Murdock really know his maybe-bride-to-be? Daredevil struggles with his off-kilter radar sense, all while trying to blow the cover on Glenn Industries! Plus, is Turk the next Stilt-Man?
description.17: Stark International is attacked by two unmanned World War II aircrafts leaving much of the staff critically injured. Iron Man must solve the mystery behind the seemingly unprovoked attack.
description.18: Our hero tests his strength with two new foes- the Dark Man and his bride, Desire!
description.19: The FF battle Latverian Doombots before the true Doctor Doom is revived!
description.20: Charles Xavier and Magneto are in WWII-era and must stop the Nazi Baron Strucker and the hordes of Hydra.
description.23: Zeus decrees a day of peace and quiet throughout Mount Olympus, but that doesn't sit well with the ever-energetic Hercules.
description.24: An epic battle ensues between Spider-Man, Cobra and Mr. Hyde! Will Spider-Man prevail and manage to save the lives of his friends?
description.25: Hawkeye must face his past after an old circus colleague is threatened by Taskmaster. Featuring Scott Lang as Ant-Man!
description.26: It's Captain America and the Howling Cammandos! What more can we say, but... WA-HOOO!
description.32: Vader reveals the existence of an Imperial spy in the Rebels ranks that strikes to the heart of Luke. Plus, who is the Emperor's Hand?
description.37: Cloak and Dagger return and their war on drugs continues!  Can Spider-Man stop the duo from going over the line?
description.38: Foggy "Guts" Nelson begins an explosive investigation on Heather and Glenn Industries. But the trail leads straight to Kingpin! Daredevil's hyper-senses are damaged in an explosion, leaving Foggy and Turk in dire straits!
description.39: An underwater adventure! Tony is developing aquatic armor to add to the Iron Man armory. Meanwhile, Stark International gives the go-ahead for Project Neptune, a new initiative for a hydro-powered generator. But why is AIM so fascinated in this project? And what will they do to acquire Project Neptune's blueprints?
description.40: In a twist of events, Thor must fight alongside the Menagerie to help Odin defeat the Wolflings!
description.41: Any What If? question you've ever had, answered in this jam-packed issue! What If the Invisible Girl dyed her hair? What If Aunt May were Ant-Man? And finally- what If the Watcher were a stand-up comedian? Brace yourselves, True Believers!
description.42: Sue endures a pesky interview, followed by an attack on the Baxter Building! Will Sue save her teammates from this unidentified yet strangely familiar attacker?
description.43: Belasco and his demon hordes are looking to use Illyana for their nefarious purposes.  Can the X-Men save Colossus's sister?
description.46: A despondent Strange reminisces about happier times with Clea, in his role as both tutor and partner.
description.47: X-Man Angel pitches in on the search for Alison’s mother, while Dazzler gets new sound equipment from the Fantastic Four.
description.48: In a bar brawl, Spider-Man finds out that "a Cobra is deadliest when cornered"! As if one villain isn't enough, our hero must also face the wrath of Mr. Hyde!
description.49: Egghead attempts to re-form the Masters of Evil, and his plans might just work! Hawkeye and She-Hulk continue their friendly feuding, while Jan finds herself "reacquainted" with an old flame.
description.50: When Sam Wilson's nephew is shot, trying to prevent a robbery, Cap and Falc team up to solve the sudden upsurge of criminal activity in Harlem! But things get weirder when the Vermin enters the fray.
description.51: Any What If? question you've ever had, answered in this jam-packed issue! What If the Invisible Girl dyed her hair? What If Aunt May were Ant-Man? And finally- what If the Watcher were a stand-up comedian? Brace yourselves, True Believers!
description.52: Luke is full of grief over a Rebel's death. Has the Force betrayed him?
description.53: Which team has won the Contest of Champions?! Where the Grandmaster is concerned, there may be no winner at all...
description.55: A mythic chapter from the legend of Thor! Will Thor stand mightiest amongst the other Gods of Men?
description.61: Valkyrie returns! Reunited with her physical form, Brunnhilde takes on Amora in an Asgardian clash for the ages! Guest-starring the Amazing Spider-Man!
description.65: With only four full-time members, the Avengers must fill up their team roster! Will Spider-Man finally accept his bid as one of Earth's Mightiest Heroes? Will Hawkeye be able to bury past grudges and rejoin the ranks? A new team of Avengers will be formed by the end of this issue!
description.66: Cap enters into the "rasslin'" ring in a challenge match against the mystery man known as "X". Cap's got this in the bag... Right?
description.67: When Daredevil and Punisher finally reach Hogman, the unlikely duo clash over what to do with him.
description.68: While presenting new feeding equipment at the Long Island Zoo, Tony Stark is attacked by the Serpent Squad. What did Iron Man do to provoke such an attack? And how did the Serpent Squad acquire their serpentine abilities?
description.69: Thor confronts Loki about the Menagerie plaguing Chicago. Will the Viking chalice be destroyed?
description.70: Frankie Raye makes a decision that will save the lives of everyone on Earth! Meanwhile, trouble with the Latverian Embassy could spell disaster for the team.
description.71: The immortal Dracula attempts to make Storm his undead bride.  But Ororo isn't going to be turned to a vampire without a fight.
description.74: TWO CONTESTS IN ONE! Our heroes must compete against each other, hoping that the path to victory leads them back to good ol' Earth!
description.77: Angel calls on the X-MEN to help him in the battle for the SAVAGE LAND! Hawkeye takes on white-collar crime!
description.78: Dazzler’s time with the Angel is derailed by sinister Spider-Villain Doctor Octopus!
description.79: Luke and other brave rebels pose as Imperials to strike at the Empire!
description.86: Doctor Strange ventures back in time to ancient Egypt and discovers the Fantastic Four, who've been enslaved by the time-traveling villain, Rama-Tut!
description.87: Enthralled by the Enchantress! The Asgardian sorceress uses the Defenders to steal the Rose of Purity for herself! How can the team save Valkyrie's soul if they can't even save themselves?
description.91: Moondragon continues to manipulate ally and foe alike with her telepathic powers. But has Drax the Destroyer had enough of her mind games? Plus, Moondragon faces the judgment of Odin after her enchantment spell on Thor goes awry!
description.92: Cap finds himself in a messy situation when he comes to the aid of an old friend. Can Cap protect his friend? And at what cost? Don't miss out as Captain America faces the Purple Fibered Monster!
description.93: When a young girl dies, her brother, Punisher, and Daredevil all hunt down the dealer responsible for her death.
description.94: After saving commuters at the Roosevelt Island tramway, Iron Man must investigate a member of his staff. Al Bido, an amnesiac janitor at Stark International, has a flair for complex chemical structures. After seeing the staff psychologist in order to recover his memories, Bido realizes that he is none other than sworn Iron Man enemy, Diablo!
description.96: Donald Blake's enjoying his newfound freedom in Chicago...until an ancient Viking chalice unleashes some evil spirits!
description.97: Dazzler, Marvel's resident Disco Queen, a herald of Galactus! Think she's ill-suited for the job? Take a read before jumping to conclusions! Plus, Iron Man's sucked into a time vortex- and he's landed in the legendary court of King Arthur!
description.98: The once-mighty Galactus must be stopped before he devours Earth! The FF are joined by a few friends- the Avengers, Spider-Man and Daredevil for this epic battle! All followed by a shocking twist and change of heart!
description.99: Storm, Wolverine, and Carol Danvers sneak into the Pentagon, but find Rogue in the halls of power!

0.text: Power Man and Iron Fist become the body guards to the turbulent rock star Rip Chord!

2.text: Even if he escapes the clutches of Fu Manchu, Shang-Chi will have to make it past the Death Dealer and his father's experiments - a dungeon of weaponized animals.

5.text: Scarlet acts as a free agent to dissemble the mob’s grip over the city…and Moon Knight is hard-pressed to stop her.

6.text: Banished from Olympus until he learns to be humble, Hercules has a hard time adjusting to life away from home.

8.text: Jackdaw steals fighter robot Megalith from the Gamma Base!

9.text: Come on, make Logan's day. He dares you. Writer Chris Claremont and artist Frank Miller send Wolverine to Japan in the feral mutant's first ferocious limited series.

He's the best there is at what he does. But what he does isn't very
nice. See Wolverine do lots of not-nice things, like fighting a bear in
the Canadian Rockies! Sword-fighting with one of his greatest foes, Lord
Shingen! And fighting for the honor of his lady love, Mariko Yashida,
against...her husband?!?
Come on, make Logan's day.  He dares you.  Frank Miller, artist extraordinaire, shows off Wolverine's shiny claws and winning smile in the feral mutant's first limited series.

10.text: The threat of Silvermane rachets up when he gets a new cyborg body. Can Spider-Man stop Cloak and Dagger from killing Silvermane?

11.text: Patsy Walker, the Daughter of Satan?!

12.text: The Sphinx is back and trying to reconstruct the source of his power - the Ka Stone! Can the Thing prevent him from rising to power once again?

15.text: The Inhuman Black Bolt answers the call to help Dazzler take down the Absorbing Man!

21.text: Night-stalker Morpheus has finally caught up to Moon Knight at his mansion in Maine. Are Marlene and Frenchie in danger too? And is this a battle for Moon Knight…or Steven Grant?

22.text: The Heroes for Hire investigate a trucker route where drivers keep mysteriously disappearing.

23.text: Zeus decrees a day of peace and quiet throughout Mount Olympus, but that doesn't sit well with the ever-energetic Hercules.

27.text: Who is Ramona Starr, AKA a “Stranger in Paradise”?

28.text: Fu Manchu gets the upper hand over his son when a giant scorpion poisons Shang-Chi.

33.text: Devil-Slayer is confronted with an existential crisis, one he is ill equipped to solve himself.

35.text: Hulk goes through bullets and grenades just to get “home” to Betty and Rick.

36.text: Spider-Woman helps the Impossible Man track down his missing wife, the Impossible Woman!

37.text: Cloak and Dagger return and their war on drugs continues!  Can Spider-Man stop the duo from going over the line?

47.text: X-Man Angel pitches in on the search for Alison’s mother, while Dazzler gets new sound equipment from the Fantastic Four.

54.text: Has Marc Spector finally cracked? After visiting Morpheus, Moon Knight finds himself haunted by a mysterious figure in black. Is this mere hallucination or something far more sinister?

55.text: A mythic chapter from the legend of Thor! Will Thor stand mightiest amongst the other Gods of Men?

56.text: In a revenge plan gone wrong, Sabretooth ends up attacking Harmony instead of Misty Knight, leaving her with some serious injuries! Luke is out to avenge Harmony, and Power Man is right there with him!

57.text: Shang-Chi's former employer, Sir Denis, suddenly finds himself completely destitute - how will they finance their next deadly mission?

60.text: Ka-Zar steps into a noir-ish state of mind in this offbeat, detective adventure.

61.text: Valkyrie returns! Reunited with her physical form, Brunnhilde takes on Amora in an Asgardian clash for the ages! Guest-starring the Amazing Spider-Man!

63.text: Bruce realizes how dangerous the Hulk power can be when he destroys an alien seed supply that could’ve possibly ended world hunger…

72.text: A giant robot attacks and Spider-Man must swing in to assist the police! But what is the secret behind this robot and how is it connected to one of Spider-Man's earliest villains?

73.text: Ka-Zar stands to lose it all in this gut punch of an issue.

78.text: Dazzler’s time with the Angel is derailed by sinister Spider-Villain Doctor Octopus!

80.text: Shang-Chi battles Fu Manchu's most dangerous assassin in this fan favorite.

84.text: The God of Vengeance sinks his teeth into a worthy victim. Will Moon Knight be able to uphold his divine obligation to Khonshu? You bet! Plus, a zombie spook fest featuring Brother Voodoo!

85.text: Warhawk is once again loose on the streets, attacking Asian civilians in his twisted way of getting back at the Vietnamese.  Power Man and Iron Fist take care of the menace once and for all!

86.text: Doctor Strange ventures back in time to ancient Egypt and discovers the Fantastic Four, who've been enslaved by the time-traveling villain, Rama-Tut!

87.text: Enthralled by the Enchantress! The Asgardian sorceress uses the Defenders to steal the Rose of Purity for herself! How can the team save Valkyrie's soul if they can't even save themselves?

89.text: Bruce Banner makes new discoveries about his Hulk powers while fighting Wendigo! Sasquatch of Alpha Flight guest-stars.
